      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(memory): align session file counter denominator with indexer filter (fixes #77338)",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\n`openclaw memory status` reports `sessions · N/M` where N > M (numerator exceeds denominator) because the denominator scanner uses a simpler `.endsWith(\".jsonl\")` filter while the indexer uses the canonical `isUsageCountedSessionTranscriptFileName()` function that excludes `.reset.*` and `.deleted.*` artifacts. This causes the session counter to show overflow on any container that has accumulated reset/tombstone files.\n\n## What does this PR do?\n\nAligns the `scanSessionFiles` denominator filter in `extensions/memory-core/src/cli.runtime.ts` with the indexer by using the canonical `isUsageCountedSessionTranscriptFileName()` helper from the plugin SDK, matching the pattern already used in `src/infra/session-cost-usage.ts:413`.\n\n## Related Issue\n\nFixes #77338\n\n## Type of Change\n\n- [x] Bug fix (non-breaking)\n- [x] AI-assisted (Hermes Agent)\n\n## Changes Made\n\n- `extensions/memory-core/src/cli.runtime.ts`: Import `isUsageCountedSessionTranscriptFileName` from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/memory-core-host-engine-qmd` and replace `.endsWith(\".jsonl\")` in `scanSessionFiles` denominator filter\n\n## How to Test\n\n1. `pnpm test:extension memory-core` — all 64 test files, 915 tests pass\n2. `pnpm build` — dist bundle includes the canonical filter function\n3. Verify `dist/cli.runtime-*.js` uses `isUsageCountedSessionTranscriptFileName` instead of `.endsWith(\".jsonl\")`\n\n## Evidence\n\n- **Behavior addressed:** `openclaw memory status` shows `sessions · N/M` where N > M because the denominator scanner counts only `.jsonl` files while the indexer also ingests `.jsonl.reset.TIMESTAMP.Z` and `.jsonl.deleted.TIMESTAMP.Z` artifacts\n- **Environment tested:** macOS 26.4.1, Node v24.3.0, pnpm build + test:extension memory-core\n- **Steps run after the patch:**\n```\n$ grep -n 'isUsageCountedSessionTranscriptFileName\\|endsWith.*jsonl' extensions/memory-core/src/cli.runtime.ts\n12:import { isUsageCountedSessionTranscriptFileName } from \"openclaw/plugin-sdk/memory-core-host-engine-qmd\";\n530:      (entry) => entry.isFile() && isUsageCountedSessionTranscriptFileName(entry.name),\n```\n```\n$ node -e \"const fs=require('fs'); const c=fs.readFileSync('dist/cli.runtime-BzTodZ17.js','utf8'); console.log('has canonical filter:', c.includes('isUsageCountedSessionTranscriptFileName')); console.log('has old pattern:', c.includes('.endsWith(\\\".jsonl\\\")'));\"\nhas canonical filter: true\nhas old pattern: false\n```\n```\n$ pnpm test:extension memory-core\n Test Files  64 passed (64)\n      Tests  915 passed (915)\n```\n- **Observed result after fix:** The bundled CLI runtime now uses the canonical `isUsageCountedSessionTranscriptFileName()` filter for the session file counter denominator, matching the indexer's behavior. The old `.endsWith(\".jsonl\")` pattern is removed from the dist output.\n- **What was not tested:** Running `openclaw memory status` against a live container with accumulated `.reset.*`/`.deleted.*` files (requires production data)\n\n",
        "branch": "fix/memory-session-counter-overflow-v7",
